Ace Nollywood star Richard Mofe-Damijo has disclosed a top-secret therapy he employs in relieving stress. According to the veteran actor, one sure way to relieve stress especially when he’s out of the country is doing his laundry himself. The fashion guru, who recently turned 60, noted it has same calming effect on his being just as shaving. He wrote: “One of my secret therapy for relieving stress when I travel is doing my laundry myself. “I love to walk to the reception, pick up quarters for the machines and the soap and just go the laundry room and do my thing. “Next to shaving it has an amazing calming effect on me.”